Latest CI:

* Homebrew [![Build Status](https://build.osrfoundation.org/buildStatus/icon?job=gazebo-ci-pr_any-homebrew-amd64&build=1738)](https://build.osrfoundation.org/job/gazebo-ci-pr_any-homebrew-amd64/1738/)
* Xenial [![Build Status](https://build.osrfoundation.org/buildStatus/icon?job=gazebo-ci-pr_any-xenial-amd64-gpu-nvidia&build=858)](https://build.osrfoundation.org/job/gazebo-ci-pr_any-xenial-amd64-gpu-nvidia/858/)

When you tackle the deprecation warning, you could also make this change that fixes a warning on my compiler:

```
diff -r afa33c6e2b98 plugins/KeysToCmdVelPlugin.cc
--- a/plugins/KeysToCmdVelPlugin.cc     Fri Aug 30 16:42:13 2019 +0200
+++ b/plugins/KeysToCmdVelPlugin.cc     Fri Aug 30 11:33:44 2019 -0700
@@ -325,7 +325,7 @@
 /////////////////////////////////////////////////
 void KeysToCmdVelPlugin::OnKeyPress(ConstAnyPtr &_msg)
 {
-  const auto key = static_cast<const unsigned int>(_msg->int_value());
+  const auto key = static_cast<unsigned int>(_msg->int_value());

   double linearVel = 0., angularVel = 0.;
   bool linearVelSet = false, angularVelSet = false;
```

The ABI could be ok since the new functions are not pure virtual. The ABI checker will tell: [![Build Status](https://build.osrfoundation.org/buildStatus/icon?job=gazebo-abichecker-any_to_any-xenial-amd64&build=834)](https://build.osrfoundation.org/job/gazebo-abichecker-any_to_any-xenial-amd64/834/)

If it does break ABI, we'll need an ugly fix, or this should be targeted at gazebo11.

